Adopting crypto as legal tender is not just about making it easier to buy and sell goods and services, it's about giving people greater control over their own financial futures. Let's work together to create a more inclusive and equitable future for all.

We should be working on a global scale, educating and building partnerships with governments and businesses in countries around the world. Crypto has the potential to be a powerful tool for financial inclusion and to improve the lives of people in every corner of the world.
I believe that if 7.7 billion people on Earth adopt crypto as legal tender, the 300 million people in the US will eventually follow suit.

This is a ambitious goal, but I am confident that with hard work and dedication, we can make it a reality.

So, an important paper at least. But even months after Liu made the announcement, no one from the crypto world, crypto media at least, has ever looked in it. People should have known better what was coming.

â€œIt is certain that in specific historical periods and systems, peopleâ€™s self-inflated persuasive power and impetuosity are major causes of crises. A relevant question thus arises: Does the rational actor hypothesis of economics hold true forever?â€

â€œAs described by the US economist John Galbraith, when the economy is overheated, no one doubts the continued inflation of the bubble. Instead of accepting reasons that cool their minds, people seek reasons that justify their blind adventures.â€

â€œWith a general impulsive mindset and encouraged by an easy monetary environment and financial innovations centered on leveraging up, people rushed into highly risky speculative activities with borrowed money, contributing to enormous asset bubbles.â€

â€œPeople would easily buy various stories of speculative miracles, and their avarice and forgetfulness ballooned to an unheard-of degree. Few people could resist the temptation of indus- trial bubbles.â€

â€œThe epic industrial growth and gargantuan gaps in incomes and distributions before the two crises distorted public psychology in the capitalist world. A yearning to change their social status had spurred people to dream about making huge fortunes overnight. â€œ

BTW, Liu is an old friend of Ray Dalio since the early 1990s. The paper was an research assignment from the top leadership after 2008 crisis. Harvard published its English translation in 2014. I am quoting a few paragraphs from the paper as followings. Make your own judgement.

The crypto world got to know Vice Premier Liu He when he announced the China ban earlier this year. But I am surprised few people brought up Liuâ€™s most famous academic work to trace where he is coming from. https://t.co/gAV8w3vXbr
Certainly there are still many open questions on such venture. But I do believe the historic pendulum is moving to that direction.
Thus a Cryptoist Civilizational Empire would emerge, open to anyone anywhere, especially for the ones that can be liberated from the incompetence of local authorities.

What makes both the American and Chinese systems work is a set of universal and civilizational ideas, traditions and standards. And in the digital era when geo-borders are just parameters, the codes for the civilizational empire in the cloud can be engraved on codes.
